flowchart TD
  A[Trigger: Replenishment pull signal from production line.]
  A --> N1[Stream: DDM/Crawler - Receive replenishment pull signal from production line.]
  N1 --> N2[Stream: STREAMS - Retrieve current inventory levels and material requirements.]
  N2 --> N3{PB: Process Builder - Sequence production line kits based on material requirements.}
  N3 -->|Primary| N4[PB: Remote Functions - Execute Just-in-Sequence deliveries to the assembly line.]
  N4 --> N5[PB: CWB Lifecycle - Monitor and adjust internal material movements and tugger operations.]
  N5 --> N6[PB: Notification - Remove empty containers from the production line.]
  N6 --> Z1[Outcome: Reduced line stoppages, optimized sequence accuracy, and minimized material handling costs.]
  N3 -->|Insufficient inventory levels detected.| B1[Trigger emergency replenishment from suppliers.]
  B1 --> O1[Outcome: Maintain production continuity.]
  O1 --> End[End]
  N3 -->|Unexpected line stoppage occurs.| B2[Adjust JIS delivery schedule and notify relevant teams.]
  B2 --> O2[Outcome: Minimize downtime and realign material flow.]
  O2 --> End[End]
  N3 -->|High waste generation from empty cont...| B3[Implement recycling or disposal strategies.]
  B3 --> O3[Outcome: Reduce waste and associated costs.]
  O3 --> End[End]
  Z1 --> End[End]